Data Collection Method: Jamar Count Board (Unit # D4-5870)
1) Sherrills Ford Elementary School’s driveway is the eastbound leg
of the studied intersection and was in session on the date of the
count, as were all Catawba County Schools. The school’s
principal, Shelly Black was notified of the count.
4) Area lighting was not present at the count location.
5) No highway construction was observed that impacted normal
6) Data collection equipment was operating correctly at time of
7) Counter took a break from 9:00 – 9:15 AM. Data for this period was interpolated.
8) Counter Notes: A deputy sheriff served as the school crossing guard and directed traffic at the intersection
from 7:25 AM to 8:10 AM and from 2:45 PM to 3:10 PM.
